<br />


	
            <p><br>Our group's major thrust is relationships among processing, properties and structure as well as the development of new materials and processes for energy, microelectronic, optoelectronic and biomedical applications.</p>
<h2>WHAT WE DO</h2>

           
<ul>
                <li>Thin film deposition</li>
                <li>Vacuum systems & reactor design</li>
				<li>Atomic layer deposition</li>
				<li>In-situ probing of surface chemical phenomena</li>
				<li>Novel materials for energy, microelectronic and optoelectronic applications</li>
                <li>Flexible electronics, screen printing & gravure printing</li>
				<li>Heterogeneous catalysis and surface chemistry</li>
                <li>Orthopaedic and dental implant surface functionalization</li>
				<li>Surface functionalization of biomaterials</li>
				<a href="publications.html">visit our Publications page for more information</a>
            </ul>
            

